verses.text_plain: Now these are the priests and the Levites that went up with Zerubbabel the son of Shealtiel, and Jeshua: Seraiah, Jeremiah, Ezra,
verses.verse_html: 1Now these are the priests and the Levites that went up with Zerubbabel the son of Shealtiel, and Jeshua: Seraiah, Jeremiah, Ezra,

verses.text_plain: Amariah, Malluch, Hattush,
verses.verse_html:
2Amariah, Malluch, Hattush, ▼

verses.text_plain: Shemaiah, and Joiarib, Jedaiah,
verses.verse_html: 6Shemaiah, and Joiarib, Jedaiah,

verses.text_plain: Sallu, Amok, Hilkiah, Jedaiah. These were the chief of the priests and of their brethren in the days of Jeshua.
verses.verse_html:
7Sallu, Amok, Hilkiah, Jedaiah. These were the chief of the priests and of their brethren in the days of Jeshua. ▼
▼ Sallu: also called, Sallai

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Sallu: also called, Sallai

verses.text_plain: Moreover the Levites: Jeshua, Binnui, Kadmiel, Sherebiah, Judah, and Mattaniah, which was over the thanksgiving, he and his brethren.
verses.verse_html:
8Moreover the Levites: Jeshua, Binnui, Kadmiel, Sherebiah, Judah, and Mattaniah, which was over the thanksgiving, he and his brethren. ▼
▼ the thanksgiving: that is, the psalms of thanksgiving

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the thanksgiving: that is, the psalms of thanksgiving
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the thanksgiving: that is, the psalms of thanksgiving

verses.text_plain: Also Bakbukiah and Unni, their brethren, were over against them in the watches.
verses.verse_html: 9Also Bakbukiah and Unni, their brethren, were over against them in the watches.

tokens.text: over against them in the watches

verses.text_plain: And Jeshua begat Joiakim, Joiakim also begat Eliashib, and Eliashib begat Joiada,
verses.verse_html: 10And Jeshua begat Joiakim, Joiakim also begat Eliashib, and Eliashib begat Joiada,

verses.text_plain: And Joiada begat Jonathan, and Jonathan begat Jaddua.
verses.verse_html: 11And Joiada begat Jonathan, and Jonathan begat Jaddua.

verses.text_plain: And in the days of Joiakim were priests, the chief of the fathers: of Seraiah, Meraiah; of Jeremiah, Hananiah;
verses.verse_html: 12And in the days of Joiakim were priests, the chief of the fathers: of Seraiah, Meraiah; of Jeremiah, Hananiah;

verses.text_plain: Of Ezra, Meshullam; of Amariah, Jehohanan;
verses.verse_html: 13Of Ezra, Meshullam; of Amariah, Jehohanan;

verses.text_plain: Of Melicu, Jonathan; of Shebaniah, Joseph;
verses.verse_html: 14Of Melicu, Jonathan; of Shebaniah, Joseph;

verses.text_plain: Of Harim, Adna; of Meraioth, Helkai;
verses.verse_html: 15Of Harim, Adna; of Meraioth, Helkai;

verses.text_plain: Of Iddo, Zechariah; of Ginnethon, Meshullam;
verses.verse_html: 16Of Iddo, Zechariah; of Ginnethon, Meshullam;

verses.text_plain: Of Abijah, Zichri; of Miniamin, of Moadiah, Piltai;
verses.verse_html: 17Of Abijah, Zichri; of Miniamin, of Moadiah, Piltai;

verses.text_plain: Of Bilgah, Shammua; of Shemaiah, Jehonathan;
verses.verse_html: 18Of Bilgah, Shammua; of Shemaiah, Jehonathan;

verses.text_plain: And of Joiarib, Mattenai; of Jedaiah, Uzzi;
verses.verse_html: 19And of Joiarib, Mattenai; of Jedaiah, Uzzi;

verses.text_plain: Of Sallai, Kallai; of Amok, Eber;
verses.verse_html: 20Of Sallai, Kallai; of Amok, Eber;

verses.text_plain: Of Hilkiah, Hashabiah; of Jedaiah, Nethaneel.
verses.verse_html: 21Of Hilkiah, Hashabiah; of Jedaiah, Nethaneel.

verses.text_plain: The Levites in the days of Eliashib, Joiada, and Johanan, and Jaddua, were recorded chief of the fathers: also the priests, to the reign of Darius the Persian.
verses.verse_html: 22The Levites in the days of Eliashib, Joiada, and Johanan, and Jaddua, were recorded chief of the fathers: also the priests, to the reign of Darius the Persian.

verses.text_plain: The sons of Levi, the chief of the fathers, were written in the book of the chronicles, even until the days of Johanan the son of Eliashib.
verses.verse_html: 23The sons of Levi, the chief of the fathers, were written in the book of the chronicles, even until the days of Johanan the son of Eliashib.

verses.text_plain: And the chief of the Levites: Hashabiah, Sherebiah, and Jeshua the son of Kadmiel, with their brethren over against them, to praise and to give thanks, according to the commandment of David the man of God, ward over against ward.
verses.verse_html: 24And the chief of the Levites: Hashabiah, Sherebiah, and Jeshua the son of Kadmiel, with their brethren over against them, to praise and to give thanks, according to the commandment of David the man of God, ward over against ward.

verses.text_plain: Mattaniah, and Bakbukiah, Obadiah, Meshullam, Talmon, Akkub, were porters keeping the ward at the thresholds of the gates.
verses.verse_html:
25Mattaniah, and Bakbukiah, Obadiah, Meshullam, Talmon, Akkub, were porters keeping the ward at the thresholds of the gates. ▼
▼ thresholds: or, treasuries, or, assemblies

footnotes.body_html: ▼ thresholds: or, treasuries, or, assemblies

verses.text_plain: These were in the days of Joiakim the son of Jeshua, the son of Jozadak, and in the days of Nehemiah the governor, and of Ezra the priest, the scribe.
verses.verse_html: 26These were in the days of Joiakim the son of Jeshua, the son of Jozadak, and in the days of Nehemiah the governor, and of Ezra the priest, the scribe.

verses.text_plain: And at the dedication of the wall of Jerusalem they sought the Levites out of all their places, to bring them to Jerusalem, to keep the dedication with gladness, both with thanksgivings, and with singing, with cymbals, psalteries, and with harps.
verses.verse_html: 27And at the dedication of the wall of Jerusalem they sought the Levites out of all their places, to bring them to Jerusalem, to keep the dedication with gladness, both with thanksgivings, and with singing, with cymbals, psalteries, and with harps.

verses.text_plain: And the sons of the singers gathered themselves together, both out of the plain country round about Jerusalem, and from the villages of Netophathi;
verses.verse_html: 28And the sons of the singers gathered themselves together, both out of the plain country round about Jerusalem, and from the villages of Netophathi;

tokens.text: both out of the plain country

verses.text_plain: Also from the house of Gilgal, and out of the fields of Geba and Azmaveth: for the singers had builded them villages round about Jerusalem.
verses.verse_html: 29Also from the house of Gilgal, and out of the fields of Geba and Azmaveth: for the singers had builded them villages round about Jerusalem.

verses.text_plain: And the priests and the Levites purified themselves, and purified the people, and the gates, and the wall.
verses.verse_html: 30And the priests and the Levites purified themselves, and purified the people, and the gates, and the wall.

verses.text_plain: Then I brought up the princes of Judah upon the wall, and appointed two great companies of them that gave thanks, whereof one went on the right hand upon the wall toward the dung gate:
verses.verse_html: 31Then I brought up the princes of Judah upon the wall, and appointed two great companies of them that gave thanks, whereof one went on the right hand upon the wall toward the dung gate:

verses.text_plain: And after them went Hoshaiah, and half of the princes of Judah,
verses.verse_html: 32And after them went Hoshaiah, and half of the princes of Judah,

verses.text_plain: And Azariah, Ezra, and Meshullam,
verses.verse_html: 33And Azariah, Ezra, and Meshullam,

verses.text_plain: Judah, and Benjamin, and Shemaiah, and Jeremiah,
verses.verse_html: 34Judah, and Benjamin, and Shemaiah, and Jeremiah,

verses.text_plain: And certain of the priests’ sons with trumpets; namely, Zechariah the son of Jonathan, the son of Shemaiah, the son of Mattaniah, the son of Michaiah, the son of Zaccur, the son of Asaph:
verses.verse_html: 35And certain of the priests’ sons with trumpets; namely, Zechariah the son of Jonathan, the son of Shemaiah, the son of Mattaniah, the son of Michaiah, the son of Zaccur, the son of Asaph:

verses.text_plain: And his brethren, Shemaiah, and Azarael, Milalai, Gilalai, Maai, Nethaneel, and Judah, Hanani, with the musical instruments of David the man of God, and Ezra the scribe before them.
verses.verse_html: 36And his brethren, Shemaiah, and Azarael, Milalai, Gilalai, Maai, Nethaneel, and Judah, Hanani, with the musical instruments of David the man of God, and Ezra the scribe before them.

verses.text_plain: And at the fountain gate, which was over against them, they went up by the stairs of the city of David, at the going up of the wall, above the house of David, even unto the water gate eastward.
verses.verse_html: 37And at the fountain gate, which was over against them, they went up by the stairs of the city of David, at the going up of the wall, above the house of David, even unto the water gate eastward.

tokens.text: which was over against them, they went up

verses.text_plain: And the other company of them that gave thanks went over against them, and I after them, and the half of the people upon the wall, from beyond the tower of the furnaces even unto the broad wall;
verses.verse_html: 38And the other company of them that gave thanks went over against them, and I after them, and the half of the people upon the wall, from beyond the tower of the furnaces even unto the broad wall;

verses.text_plain: And from above the gate of Ephraim, and above the old gate, and above the fish gate, and the tower of Hananeel, and the tower of Meah, even unto the sheep gate: and they stood still in the prison gate.
verses.verse_html: 39And from above the gate of Ephraim, and above the old gate, and above the fish gate, and the tower of Hananeel, and the tower of Meah, even unto the sheep gate: and they stood still in the prison gate.

verses.text_plain: So stood the two companies of them that gave thanks in the house of God, and I, and the half of the rulers with me:
verses.verse_html: 40So stood the two companies of them that gave thanks in the house of God, and I, and the half of the rulers with me:

verses.text_plain: And the priests; Eliakim, Maaseiah, Miniamin, Michaiah, Elioenai, Zechariah, and Hananiah, with trumpets;
verses.verse_html: 41And the priests; Eliakim, Maaseiah, Miniamin, Michaiah, Elioenai, Zechariah, and Hananiah, with trumpets;

verses.text_plain: And Maaseiah, and Shemaiah, and Eleazar, and Uzzi, and Jehohanan, and Malchijah, and Elam, and Ezer. And the singers sang loud, with Jezrahiah their overseer.
verses.verse_html:
42And Maaseiah, and Shemaiah, and Eleazar, and Uzzi, and Jehohanan, and Malchijah, and Elam, and Ezer. And the singers sang loud, with Jezrahiah their overseer. ▼
▼ sang…: Heb. made their voice to be heard

footnotes.body_text: ▼ sang…: Heb. made their voice to be heard
footnotes.body_html: ▼ sang…: Heb. made their voice to be heard

verses.text_plain: Also that day they offered great sacrifices, and rejoiced: for God had made them rejoice with great joy: the wives also and the children rejoiced: so that the joy of Jerusalem was heard even afar off.
verses.verse_html: 43Also that day they offered great sacrifices, and rejoiced: for God had made them rejoice with great joy: the wives also and the children rejoiced: so that the joy of Jerusalem was heard even afar off.

verses.text_plain: And at that time were some appointed over the chambers for the treasures, for the offerings, for the firstfruits, and for the tithes, to gather into them out of the fields of the cities the portions of the law for the priests and Levites: for Judah rejoiced for the priests and for the Levites that waited.
verses.verse_html:
44And at that time were some appointed over the chambers for the treasures, for the offerings, for the firstfruits, and for the tithes, to gather into them out of the fields of the cities the portions of the law for the priests and Levites: for Judah rejoiced for the priests and for the Levites that waited. ▼
▼ of the law: that is, appointed by the law
 , ▼
▼ for Judah…: Heb. for the joy of Judah
 , ▼
▼ waited: Heb. stood

footnotes.body_html: ▼ of the law: that is, appointed by the law

footnotes.body_html: ▼ for Judah…: Heb. for the joy of Judah

verses.text_plain: And both the singers and the porters kept the ward of their God, and the ward of the purification, according to the commandment of David, and of Solomon his son.
verses.verse_html: 45And both the singers and the porters kept the ward of their God, and the ward of the purification, according to the commandment of David, and of Solomon his son.

verses.text_plain: For in the days of David and Asaph of old there were chief of the singers, and songs of praise and thanksgiving unto God.
verses.verse_html: 46For in the days of David and Asaph of old there were chief of the singers, and songs of praise and thanksgiving unto God.

verses.text_plain: And all Israel in the days of Zerubbabel, and in the days of Nehemiah, gave the portions of the singers and the porters, every day his portion: and they sanctified holy things unto the Levites; and the Levites sanctified them unto the children of Aaron.
verses.verse_html:
47And all Israel in the days of Zerubbabel, and in the days of Nehemiah, gave the portions of the singers and the porters, every day his portion: and they sanctified holy things unto the Levites; and the Levites sanctified them unto the children of Aaron. ▼
▼ sanctified: that is, set apart

footnotes.body_html: ▼ sanctified: that is, set apart
